From ca235148b4c8ba1b7ee234a0ac57b5760f853839 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 22:35:19 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: an7563: rebrand failsafe Web UI

Replace the bare-bones recovery pages with an AIROHA-branded
card-based layout: stacked MEDIATEK / AIROHA wordmark in the
header, rounded card body, modern primary/secondary buttons and
status icons (ok / err / warn / work) for the
success/fail/validate-fail/flashing states. Implemented purely
with HTML + CSS (no inline SVG, raster image or external font).

The server-side contract is preserved: the 32-character "X" md5
placeholder and 10-character "Y" byte-count placeholder in
upload.html, the URI handler bindings (/, /upload, /flashing,
/result, /style.css, 404 fallback) and the /result polling done
by flashing.html are unchanged.

Total fsdata grows from 3,063 bytes to 11,264 bytes; the
.incbin embedding in failsafe/fsdata/embed.S makes the delta
land byte-for-byte in u-boot.bin.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
